        ## Notice for React examples

        The function `React.createElement` is aliased as `$` allowing
        to write simple nested things in coffeescript like this:

            $ 'div', null,
              $ Molecule.Button, null, 'Button A'
              $ Molecule.Button, null, 'Button B'

        This will render a div tag containing two buttons without
        using `React.DOM` or `createFactory`. This style is not necessary
        but only a personal preference.
